text.paragraph:
Dose reduction is recommended when administering valganciclovir to patients with renal impairment [see Dosage and Administration (

                                 2.5

                              ), see Warnings and Precautions (
                                 5.2
                              ), Clinical Pharmacology (
                                 12.3
                              )].

Experience with Valganciclovir Tablets: An overdose of valganciclovir could possibly result in increased renal toxicity [see Dosage and Administration (

      2.5

   ), see Use in Specific Populations (
      8.6
   )]. Because ganciclovir is dialyzable, dialysis may be useful in reducing serum concentrations in patients who have received an overdose of valganciclovir [see Clinical 
Pharmacology (
      12.3
   )]. Adequate hydration should be maintained. The use of hematopoietic growth factors should be considered [see Warnings and Precautions (
      5.1
   ) and Clinical Pharmacology (
      12.3
   )].
